President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Jeffrey R. Moreland as the Director of the Amtrak Board of Directors. Moreland is currently serving as the Vice Chairman of the Amtrak Board and has been a member since 2010. He previously held various positions at Burlington Northern Santa Fe Railway Company, including Executive Vice President for Public Affairs. Moreland also has experience working at the Securities and Exchange Commission. He holds a B.S. degree from Georgetown University, a J.D. from Catholic University School of Law, and an M.B.A. from the University of Chicago.